    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            .task { background: maroon; }<br>
            .count { background: yellow; }
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>4.2.1 Hexadecimal Colors</h2>
    <p>Hexadecimal color values consist of a pound, or hash, #, followed by a three- or six-character figure...</p>

   

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            .task { background: #800000; }<br>
            .count { background: #ff0; }
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="figure">
        <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcR7yY-zImw32uM2ukRqiAhCTHlzAKZMbYbzzQ&s" alt="Figure 2: Photoshop Color Picker">
        <div class="figure-caption">Figure 2: The color picker of Photoshop showing hexadecimal and RGB values</div>
    </div>

    <h2>4.2.3 RGB & RGBa Colors</h2>
    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            .task { background: rgb(128, 0, 0); }<br>
            .count { background: rgb(255, 255, 0); }<br>
            .task { background: rgba(128, 0, 0, .25); }<br>
            .count { background: rgba(255, 255, 0, 1); }
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>4.2.4 HSL & HSLa Colors</h2>
    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            .task { background: hsl(0, 100%, 25%); }<br>
            .count { background: hsl(60, 100%, 50%); }<br>
            .task { background: hsla(0, 100%, 25%, .25); }<br>
            .count { background: hsla(60, 100%, 50%, 1); }
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>4.3 Lengths</h2>
    <p>Length values within CSS are similar to colors in that there are a handful of different types of values for length...</p>

    <h3>4.3.1 Absolute Lengths</h3>
    <p>Absolute length values are the simplest length values, as they are fixed to a physical measurement, such as inches, centimeters, or millimeters. The most popular absolute unit of measurement is known as the pixel and is represented by the px unit notation.</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            p { font-size: 14px; }
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>4.4 Relative Lengths</h3>
    <h4>4.4.1 Percentages</h4>
    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            .col { width: 50%; }
        </div>
    </div>

    <h4>4.4.2 Em</h4>
    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            .banner { font-size: 14px; width: 5em; }
        </div>
    </div>

</div>
